ifically illiterate antivaxxers or faceless bureaucrats. Hausman reveals that vaccine skepticism is, in part, a critique of medicalization and a warning about the dangers of modern medicine rather than a glib and gullible reaction to scaremongering and misunderstanding.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAnti-vaccination movementzUnited States. 0aAnti-vaccination movement-United States. 0aVaccination of childrenxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aVaccination of children-Social aspects-United States. 0aVaccinationxSocial aspectszUnited States. 0aVaccination-Social aspects-United States. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aMedicine & Medical Issues. 4aPublic Policy.  avaccinations, pharmaceutical, bodily autonomy, citizens' health, medicalization, modern medicine.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishz978311061053608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019z9783110606386oZDB-23-DPM40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150173563940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501735639423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501735639/original  a978-3-11-061053-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  